            <div class="lesson-content">
                <h2>ASL Numbers 11 to 15</h2>

                <!-- Number 11 -->
                <p><strong>Number 11:</strong> Flick the index finger up twice. Start with the index finger extended up
                    from the palm, then quickly bend it down at the middle joint and bring it back up.</p>

                <!-- Number 12 -->
                <p><strong>Number 12:</strong> Flick the index and middle fingers up together twice. Start with these
                    fingers extended up from the palm, then quickly bend them down at their middle joints and bring them
                    back up.</p>

                <!-- Number 13 -->
                <p><strong>Number 13:</strong> Start with the index and middle fingers extended up, then bend them at
                    the knuckles and wiggle them together a few times.</p>

                <!-- Number 14 -->
                <p><strong>Number 14:</strong> Similar to 13, extend the index, middle, and ring fingers, then bend them
                    at the knuckles and wiggle them together.</p>

                <!-- Number 15 -->
                <p><strong>Number 15:</strong> Extend all fingers (except the thumb), bend them at the knuckles, and
                    wiggle them together a few times.</p>
            </div>
        </section>


        <!-- Section for ASL Numbers 16-19 -->
