            <div class="lesson-content">
                <h2>ASL Numbers 20 to 29</h2>

                <!-- Number 20 -->
                <p><strong>Number 20:</strong></p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Form a 'Y' handshape (like the peace sign), with the thumb and pinky finger extended.</li>
                    <li>Twist the wrist back and forth a couple of times while maintaining the 'Y' handshape.</li>
                </ul>

                <!-- Numbers 21 to 29 -->
                <p><strong>Numbers 21 to 29:</strong> These numbers combine the sign for 20 with subsequent units (1 to
                    9) using standard finger counting.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>21:</strong> Start with the 20 sign, then transition to extending the index finger to
                        represent '1'.</li>
                    <li><strong>22:</strong> Start with the 20 sign, then transition to extending both the index and
                        middle fingers for '2'.</li>
                    <li><strong>23:</strong> Start with the 20 sign, then transition to extending the index, middle, and
                        ring fingers for '3'.</li>
                    <li><strong>24:</strong> Start with the 20 sign, then transition to extending the index, middle,
                        ring, and pinky fingers for '4'.</li>
                    <li><strong>25:</strong> Start with the 20 sign, then show all fingers extended including the thumb
                        for '5'.</li>
                    <li><strong>26:</strong> Start with the 20 sign, then transition to the 6 sign (thumb touching the
                        pinky finger).</li>
                    <li><strong>27:</strong> Start with the 20 sign, then transition to the 7 sign (thumb touching the
                        ring finger).</li>
                    <li><strong>28:</strong> Start with the 20 sign, then transition to the 8 sign (thumb touching the
                        middle finger).</li>
                    <li><strong>29:</strong> Start with the 20 sign, then transition to the 9 sign (thumb touching the
                        index finger).</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </section>



        <!-- Section for ASL Numbers 30-39 -->
        <section class="asl-numbers-30-39">
            <div class="lesson-content">
                <h2>ASL Numbers 30 to 39</h2>

                <!-- Number 30 -->
                <p><strong>Number 30:</strong></p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Sign '3': Extend the thumb, index, and middle fingers while keeping the ring and pinky fingers
                        curled into the palm.</li>
                    <li>Followed by the sign for '0': Form an 'O' handshape by bringing all fingers together and
                        touching the thumb to the fingertips.</li>
                </ul>

                <!-- Numbers 31-39 -->
                <p><strong>Numbers 31 to 39:</strong> Sign '3', followed by the respective unit numbers (1-9).</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>31:</strong> Start with the sign for '3', then sign '1' by extending the index finger.
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>32:</strong> Start with the sign for '3', then sign '2' by extending the index and
                        middle fingers.</li>
                    <li><strong>33:</strong> Start with the sign for '3', then sign '3' again.</li>
                    <li><strong>34:</strong> Start with the sign for '3', then sign '4' by extending the index, middle,
                        ring, and pinky fingers.</li>
                    <li><strong>35:</strong> Start with the sign for '3', then sign '5' by extending all fingers and the
                        thumb.</li>
                    <li><strong>36:</strong> Start with the sign for '3', then sign '6' by touching the thumb to the
                        pinky finger.</li>
                    <li><strong>37:</strong> Start with the sign for '3', then sign '7' by touching the thumb to the
                        ring finger.</li>
                    <li><strong>38:</strong> Start with the sign for '3', then sign '8' by touching the thumb to the
                        middle finger.</li>
                    <li><strong>39:</strong> Start with the sign for '3', then sign '9' by touching the thumb to the
                        index finger.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
