        <!-- Section for ASL Number 100 -->
        <section class="asl-number-100">
            <div class="lesson-content">
                <h2>ASL Number 100</h2>

                <!-- Instruction for Number 100 -->
                <p><strong>Number 100:</strong> Sign '100' by first signing the number '1', which is done by extending
                    the index finger while keeping the rest of the fingers curled into the palm and the thumb resting
                    alongside the palm. Follow this by signing a 'C' handshape, representing 'century' or 'hundred'. The
                    'C' handshape is made by curving all fingers and the thumb to form a 'C'.</p>

                <!-- Encouragement and Instructions for Higher Numbers -->
                <p>Congratulations on learning ASL numbers from 1 to 100! For numbers beyond 100, ASL typically uses a
                    combination of the base number followed by the sign for 'hundred', 'thousand', or 'million', as
                    needed. For instance, '200' would be signed as '2' followed by the 'C' handshape for 'hundred', and
                    similarly for higher numbers. Keep practicing to master these higher numbers in ASL.</p>
            </div>
